Pre-Game Insights: Australia has a strong record in World Cup semi-finals, having won both previous meetings in 1999 and 2007.
South Africa boasts a positive win-loss record against Australia (55 to 50) and has won 15 of their last 18 meetings.
South Africa's batting lineup has been dominant, scoring four totals over 350, including a highest score of 428 against Sri Lanka.
Temba Bavuma is struggling with a hamstring strain, which could impact his availability for the match.
There is a possibility of rain affecting the match, with a reserve day available.
